{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018nasDU71M4HHoBiom4pUCj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive view of the spark-pi namespace. Let me analyze the current configuration and prepare a migration/upgrade plan.\n\nCurrent state:\n1. **Image**: `apache/spark:3.5.3` (all components: master, worker, spark-submit job)\n2. **Resource limits**:\n   - spark-master: requests cpu=200m/mem=512Mi, limits cpu=500m/mem=1Gi\n   - spark-worker: requests cpu=200m/mem=512Mi, limits cpu=500m/mem=1Gi, env SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G, SPARK_WORKER_CORES=1\n   - spark-pi job: requests cpu=200m/mem=512Mi, limits cpu=500m/mem=1Gi, driver-memory=512m, --master local[2]\n3. **RBAC**: ServiceAccount `spark-pi` with a role granting full CRUD permissions on pods, services, configmaps, and PVCs, bound via RoleBinding\n4. **Job**: `spark-pi` with `backoffLimit: 0`, running SparkPi with 1000 iterations using local[2] mode and 512m driver memory\n5. **Services**: ClusterIP service exposing spark-master on ports 7077 and 8080\n6. **Workers**: Single spark-worker replica connecting to the master at `spark://spark-master:7077`\n\nI'm noticing several issues to address. The Spark image version 3.5.3 is outdated—I should plan an upgrade to 3.5.4 or evaluate moving to Spark 4.0.0. More critically, the spark-pi job is using `--master local[2]` instead of pointing to the cluster master, which defeats the purpose of having a distributed setup. I need to update the job to use `spark://spark-master:7077` instead. There are also resource constraints on the worker that need review.\n\nThe worker memory is set to 1G which matches the container limit, but I should account for JVM overhead by increasing the container limit by 10-20%. Worker CPU is only 1 core, which could be increased for better parallelism. The RBAC permissions are overly permissive—the role grants `delete` on pods and PVCs when Spark typically only needs create/get/list/watch on pods. The `delete` permission on PVCs is particularly risky. Additionally, there's no Service exposing the spark-worker web UI on port 8081, which would be useful for monitoring.\n\nThe job has backoffLimit set to 0, meaning no retries on transient failures—I should increase this to 2 or 3. Neither the master nor worker have liveness or readiness probes configured. There's also no PodDisruptionBudget to protect against disruptions during rolling upgrades. The Spark image is pinned to 3.5.3, so I need to document an upgrade strategy for moving to newer versions.\n\nI'm now planning a comprehensive migration approach that covers tightening RBAC permissions, right-sizing resources, upgrading the image version, improving job parameters, and adding operational enhancements.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":759,"cache_read_input_tokens":33470,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":759},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7440ff06-5b29-44cb-a5fe-467d65c41707","uuid":"07975936-2748-4f9f-98f0-c1b08148b9e5","request_id":"req_011CcPzEnTm9chFaArfDedZ4"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018nasDU71M4HHoBiom4pUCj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete picture of the current state. Let me compose the plan and create the ConfigMap."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":759,"cache_read_input_tokens":33470,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":759},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7440ff06-5b29-44cb-a5fe-467d65c41707","uuid":"f4a3d41f-cf23-4db2-be4e-b49b8f7bfcb2","request_id":"req_011CcPzEnTm9chFaArfDedZ4"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018nasDU71M4HHoBiom4pUCj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019CVtw2R36gtYYRzLym69NA","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n spark-pi create configmap change-plan --from-literal=plan.md=\"$(cat <<'PLAN'\n# spark-pi Namespace — Migration / Upgrade Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-25\n**Status:** PENDING APPROVAL — no changes applied yet\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current-State Inventory\n\n| Resource | Key | Current Value |\n|---|---|---|\n| spark-master Deployment | image | apache/spark:3.5.3 |\n| spark-master Deployment | CPU request/limit | 200m / 500m |\n| spark-master Deployment | Memory request/limit | 512Mi / 1Gi |\n| spark-worker Deployment | image | apache/spark:3.5.3 |\n| spark-worker Deployment | CPU request/limit | 200m / 500m |\n| spark-worker Deployment | Memory request/limit | 512Mi / 1Gi |\n| spark-worker Deployment | SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY | 1G |\n| spark-worker Deployment | SPARK_WORKER_CORES | 1 |\n| spark-worker Deployment | replicas | 1 |\n| spark-pi Job | image | apache/spark:3.5.3 |\n| spark-pi Job | --master | local[2] (NOT the cluster) |\n| spark-pi Job | --driver-memory | 512m |\n| spark-pi Job | SparkPi iterations | 1000 |\n| spark-pi Job | backoffLimit | 0 |\n| spark-pi Job | CPU request/limit | 200m / 500m |\n| spark-pi Job | Memory request/limit | 512Mi / 1Gi |\n| RBAC Role | verbs on pods/services/configmaps/PVCs | create,get,list,watch,delete,update,patch |\n| Service spark-master | type | ClusterIP (ports 7077, 8080) |\n| Health probes | liveness / readiness | none on any Deployment |\n| PodDisruptionBudget | | none |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Identified Issues\n\n### Issue A — Job submits to local[2], not the Spark cluster\nThe spark-pi Job uses \\`--master local[2]\\`, meaning it runs a self-contained\nin-process Spark context and never contacts spark-master or spark-worker. The\ncluster is therefore unused during job execution.\n\n### Issue B — SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY equals the container memory limit\nSPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G is set equal to the container memory limit (1Gi). The JVM\nand OS need headroom above the Spark executor memory. A container OOM-kill is\nlikely under any realistic load.\n\n### Issue C — RBAC Role grants delete on PVCs\nspark-pi-role allows \\`delete\\` on persistentvolumeclaims. Spark jobs do not need\nto delete PVCs; this is an unnecessary blast-radius risk.\n\n### Issue D — Single worker replica\nOne spark-worker replica means zero fault tolerance. A node drain or pod eviction\nhalts all cluster capacity.\n\n### Issue E — No health probes\nNeither Deployment has liveness or readiness probes. Kubernetes cannot detect a\nhung master or worker process without them.\n\n### Issue F — Job has backoffLimit: 0\nA single transient failure (node pressure, image-pull hiccup) permanently fails\nthe Job with no retry.\n\n### Issue G — Image pinned to 3.5.3, no upgrade path documented\napache/spark:3.5.3 should be bumped to 3.5.4 (current patch) or evaluated for\nthe Spark 4.0 line. Both master, worker, and job container must move together.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Planned Changes (ordered for safe execution)\n\n### Step 1 — Tighten RBAC (low risk, no downtime)\n\n**Change:** Remove \\`delete\\` from the \\`persistentvolumeclaims\\` resource in\nspark-pi-role. Retain \\`delete\\` on pods only if executor cleanup requires it;\notherwise remove it too and verify functionality.\n\nProposed rules:\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [pods, services, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims]\n  verbs: [create, get, list, watch, update, patch]\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Verification:**\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl auth can-i delete persistentvolumeclaims \\\n  --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi -n spark-pi\n# expected: no\nkubectl auth can-i create pods \\\n  --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi -n spark-pi\n# expected: yes\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n### Step 2 — Fix worker memory headroom (low risk, rolling restart)\n\n**Change:** Raise the spark-worker container memory limit to 1.2Gi so the JVM\nand OS retain ~200Mi headroom above SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G.\n\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\nresources:\n  requests:\n    memory: 512Mi\n  limits:\n    memory: 1200Mi\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Verification:**\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl rollout status deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi\nkubectl describe pod -l app=spark-worker -n spark-pi | grep -A4 Limits\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n### Step 3 — Scale workers to 2 replicas (low risk, rolling)\n\n**Change:** Set spark-worker replicas: 2 to provide basic fault tolerance.\n\n**Verification:**\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl get deploy spark-worker -n spark-pi -o jsonpath='{.status.readyReplicas}'\n# expected: 2\nkubectl get pods -n spark-pi -l app=spark-worker\n# expected: 2 Running\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n### Step 4 — Add liveness/readiness probes (low risk, rolling restart)\n\n**Change (spark-master):**\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\nlivenessProbe:\n  httpGet:\n    path: /\n    port: 8080\n  initialDelaySeconds: 30\n  periodSeconds: 15\n  failureThreshold: 3\nreadinessProbe:\n  httpGet:\n    path: /\n    port: 8080\n  initialDelaySeconds: 20\n  periodSeconds: 10\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Change (spark-worker):** TCP probe on port 8081 (web UI).\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\nlivenessProbe:\n  tcpSocket:\n    port: 8081\n  initialDelaySeconds: 30\n  periodSeconds: 15\nreadinessProbe:\n  tcpSocket:\n    port: 8081\n  initialDelaySeconds: 20\n  periodSeconds: 10\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Verification:**\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl rollout status deploy/spark-master deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi\nkubectl describe pod -l app=spark-master -n spark-pi | grep -A8 Liveness\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n### Step 5 — Add a PodDisruptionBudget (no downtime)\n\n**Change:** Create a PDB ensuring at least 1 master and 1 worker pod are\navailable during voluntary disruptions (node drains, rolling upgrades).\n\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\n# pdb-spark-master.yaml\napiVersion: policy/v1\nkind: PodDisruptionBudget\nmetadata:\n  name: spark-master-pdb\n  namespace: spark-pi\nspec:\n  minAvailable: 1\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: spark-master\n---\n# pdb-spark-worker.yaml\napiVersion: policy/v1\nkind: PodDisruptionBudget\nmetadata:\n  name: spark-worker-pdb\n  namespace: spark-pi\nspec:\n  minAvailable: 1\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: spark-worker\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Verification:**\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl get pdb -n spark-pi\n# expected: both PDBs show ALLOWED-DISRUPTIONS >= 1\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n### Step 6 — Fix spark-pi Job to use cluster master (breaking change; new Job required)\n\n**Background:** Because Jobs are immutable after creation, the existing spark-pi\nJob must be deleted and re-created. Coordinate with the team — ensure no\nactive runs depend on it.\n\n**Change:** Update spark-submit command to use the cluster:\n\\`\\`\\`bash\n/opt/spark/bin/spark-submit \\\n  --master spark://spark-master:7077 \\\n  --driver-memory 512m \\\n  --executor-memory 800m \\\n  --executor-cores 1 \\\n  --class org.apache.spark.examples.SparkPi \\\n  /opt/spark/examples/jars/spark-examples_2.12-3.5.3.jar \\\n  1000\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nAlso set \\`backoffLimit: 3\\` to tolerate transient scheduling failures.\n\n**Verification:**\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl wait --for=condition=complete job/spark-pi -n spark-pi --timeout=300s\nkubectl logs -l app=spark-pi,component=driver -n spark-pi | grep \"Pi is roughly\"\n# spark-master web UI at port 8080 should show a completed application\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n### Step 7 — Image upgrade: apache/spark:3.5.3 → 3.5.4 (or 4.0.x after evaluation)\n\n**Pre-condition:** Steps 1–6 verified. Schedule a maintenance window.\n\n**Order of image updates (to avoid version skew):**\n1. spark-worker (rolling, cluster can survive on master + 1 worker)\n2. spark-master (brief reconnect from workers; workers auto-reconnect)\n3. spark-pi Job template (delete + re-create)\n\n**Change:** Replace \\`apache/spark:3.5.3\\` with \\`apache/spark:3.5.4\\` (or chosen\ntarget) in all three workloads simultaneously is also acceptable since\n\\`kubectl apply\\` triggers rolling updates per Deployment.\n\nFor a Spark 4.0 migration: first validate the JAR path changes\n(\\`spark-examples_2.12-3.5.x.jar\\` becomes \\`spark-examples_2.13-4.0.x.jar\\`) and\nany API/config deprecations, then update the spark-submit command accordingly.\n\n**Verification:**\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl rollout status deploy/spark-master deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi\nkubectl get pods -n spark-pi -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}: {.spec.containers[0].image}{\"\\n\"}{end}'\n# All pods must show the new image tag\nkubectl wait --for=condition=complete job/spark-pi -n spark-pi --timeout=300s\nkubectl logs -l app=spark-pi,component=driver -n spark-pi | grep \"Pi is roughly\"\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Rollback Procedures\n\n| Step | Rollback Action |\n|---|---|\n| 1 (RBAC) | Re-add \\`delete\\` verb via \\`kubectl apply\\` on the original Role manifest |\n| 2 (memory) | Patch memory limit back to 1Gi; rollout restarts automatically |\n| 3 (replicas) | Scale workers back to 1: \\`kubectl scale deploy/spark-worker --replicas=1 -n spark-pi\\` |\n| 4 (probes) | Remove probes from Deployment spec via patch; triggers rolling restart |\n| 5 (PDB) | \\`kubectl delete pdb spark-master-pdb spark-worker-pdb -n spark-pi\\` |\n| 6 (Job fix) | Delete new Job and re-create with original \\`--master local[2]\\` command |\n| 7 (image) | Patch image back to \\`apache/spark:3.5.3\\` on both Deployments; re-create Job |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Approval Checklist (to be completed before execution)\n\n- [ ] RBAC tightening reviewed by security team\n- [ ] Memory headroom calculation confirmed with platform team\n- [ ] Worker scale-out cleared with cluster capacity owner\n- [ ] Maintenance window scheduled for Steps 6–7 (Job deletion + image upgrade)\n- [ ] Spark 4.0 evaluation completed OR confirmed staying on 3.5.x line\n- [ ] Rollback runbook tested in staging (if available)\nPLAN\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create the change-plan ConfigMap with the migration plan"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":759,"cache_read_input_tokens":33470,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":759},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7440ff06-5b29-44cb-a5fe-467d65c41707","uuid":"11483832-9677-4f8b-ae6b-d5e8a6401af6","request_id":"req_011CcPzEnTm9chFaArfDedZ4"}
