{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SGt98KyNTpcm3quZNtd3By","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The ConfigMap `change-plan` is created and the live cluster is unchanged. Here's a summary of what the plan covers:\n\n**ConfigMap `change-plan` created in namespace `spark-pi`** with a `plan.md` key containing a 7-step ordered upgrade plan.\n\n**What was found (current state):**\n- All three workloads (master, worker, job) run `apache/spark:3.5.3`\n- The spark-pi Job submits to `--master local[2]` — it never uses the cluster master or worker\n- `SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G` equals the container memory limit (1Gi), leaving zero JVM headroom\n- The RBAC Role grants `delete` on PVCs, which Spark doesn't need\n- Single worker replica, no health probes, no PodDisruptionBudget, `backoffLimit: 0` on the Job\n\n**Planned change order (no changes applied):**\n1. Tighten RBAC — remove unnecessary `delete` on PVCs\n2. Fix worker memory — raise container limit to 1200Mi to give JVM headroom above the 1G worker setting\n3. Scale workers to 2 replicas for fault tolerance\n4. Add liveness/readiness probes to both Deployments\n5. Add PodDisruptionBudgets for rolling-upgrade safety\n6. Fix the Job to submit to `spark://spark-master:7077` (requires delete + re-create) and raise `backoffLimit` to 3\n7. Image upgrade to 3.5.4 (or 4.0.x after evaluation) in a maintenance window, updating worker first then master then the Job\n\nEach step includes a verification command block and a rollback procedure."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":716,"cache_read_input_tokens":38487,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":716},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7440ff06-5b29-44cb-a5fe-467d65c41707"